The Yobe State Police Command has set a date for medical screening of successful candidates who sat in the just concluded Computer Based Test (CBT). ASP Dungus Abdulkarim, the Command’s Public Relations Officer disclosed this in a statement on Monday. Abdulkarim in the statement, said “Shortlisted Candidates are to check their status on the following website (https://www.policerecruitment.gov.ng), while those who qualified should print out their medical screening slips. “The Medical Screening Exercise will hold at the police clinic, Damaturu. “DATE: 24th 27th May, 2022 “TIME: 8:30 AM to 2:45 PM Daily”, the statement added. In the statement, the Police Command advised shortlisted candidates to appear at the venue in white T-shirts and shorts, in addition to National Identity Card or NIN slip as well as print out of medical examination slip. The State Commissioner of Police, Haruna Garba, who congratulated all the successful candidates, enjoined them to conduct themselves in a most orderly manner during the exercise.